news.title: Chandigarh: Sector 20 colony first to be razed for group housing
news.para: The colony spread over around 2 to 3 acres has 116 houses, the smallest government accommodation -smaller than category 13 government houses - in the city, with each unit area of around 250-300 sq ft.

news.title: Govt mulling upgrading some urban local bodies as municipal corporations: Himachal Pradesh CM
news.para: ​Presiding over a review meeting of the Urban Development, Town and Country Planning and Municipal Corporations Department, he said this would not only stop unplanned construction but also ensure planned development of these fast-emerging towns.

news.title: Home loan sanctions double in three years in Gujarat
news.para: According to the latest quarterly report issued by the State Level Bankers' Committee (SLBC) on Thursday, the outstanding loans under housing finance have grown from Rs 77,065 crore in the September quarter of 2019-20 to Rs 1.51 lakh crore in the corresponding quarter of 2022-23 - up 97%.
